From b713543b2b74a5309aec4dbd929af07821594242 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: skullernet <255839533+skullernet@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 20:34:34 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 01/18] Convert memory allocation functions to use size_t.

This makes memory allocation less susceptible to integer overflow
errors.

Zone allocator can't return more than 2 GiB per call, but cumulative
size of all allocations can exceed signed 32-bit integer range if
USE_MULTI_SEGMENT is enabled. For this reason convert zone statistics to
use size_t as well.

Hunk allocator continues to use signed 32-bit integers internally
because total hunk size is limited to 2 GiB.

Check upper bound of com_zoneMegs/com_hunkMegs cvars to prevent integer
overflows.
