Subject: [PATCH 11/18] Fix broken MD3 LODs registration.

There are multiple problems with R_RegisterMD3().

First, it registers LODs in reverse order, stopping when error occurs,
and then tries to fill missing LOD slots with duplicates. But this
doesn't work due to broken logic. If error occurs some LOD slots end up
having missing/invalid data.

Fix this by registering LODs in ascending order, only incrementing
mod->numLods after LOD slot is successfully loaded. In case of errors
this gives preference to higher detail LODs which most users likely
want.

Second, strchr() is used to find and strip filename extension. This
breaks models with dot characters in path components. Use specialized
COM_GetExtension()/COM_StripExtension() functions to avoid this problem.
---
 code/renderer/tr_model.c   | 66 +++++++++++---------------------------
 code/renderervk/tr_model.c | 66 +++++++++++---------------------------
 2 files changed, 38 insertions(+), 94 deletions(-)

