From 53e8f6d587971459141e33a73d84da89138701c3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: skullernet <255839533+skullernet@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 2026 20:48:56 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 12/18] Fix some minor PVS handling issues.

inPVS() family of functions should never return true if one or both
points are inside solid leaf. If the second point is in solid, PVS row
data would be indexed with a cluster of -1, which is invalid. Arguments
are supposed to be commutative, so treat both points equally.

CM_ClusterPVS() returns data for cluster 0 when passed cluster -1, which
is incorrect for maps with visibility data. For consistency, handle
cluster -1 the same as renderer does: return a dummy PVS row of all-ones.

Don't overallocate memory for dummy PVS rows by properly dividing number
of clusters by 8.
---
